article_title: Four months in, how is Obamacare doing? – The Denver Post
article_text: Colorado officials on Monday announced they had suspended the registration of a surgical technologist who did not disclose three alcohol-related offenses on his registration renewal application. Emir Kurjak faces additional proceedings to determine whether his registration will face further discipline, according to a statement from the Division of Professions and Occupations at the Colorado Department of Regulatory Agencies.
